On Friday, MacCoffee celebrated and appreciated medics for the great role they have played in giving care to Covid-19 patients, leading to a rising number of recoveries each day. Receiving the items on behalf of the Aga Khan University Hospital, the CEO, Dr Shawn Bolouki, welcomed the initiative. “We are very thankful to MacCoffee and the Hindu Council for coming today and appreciating our staff. Hopefully, this will be the beginning of the close collaboration of working together to meet the needs of the community,” Bolouki said.